==English==

===Noun===
'''thingness'''
#The quality of a material [[thing]]; [[objectivity]]; [[actuality]]; [[reality]].

===Quotations===
* '''1994,''' Shadia B Drury, ''Alexandre Kojève'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&vid=ISBN0312120923&id=zQRKXLwDPc4C&pg=PA26&lpg=PA26&sig=zR0NpFT9gF4Mo_VTIPTm1274piI]
*: To live as a thing, to live for another and as the other expects, is to live unauthentically or in ''bad faith.'' To be true to oneself, one must reduce others to '''thingness''' and resist being so reduced.
* '''1998,''' William C Chittick, ''The Self-Disclosure of God'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&vid=ISBN0791434036&id=HKvcLT881KsC&pg=PA46&lpg=PA46&sig=MwptOcI_pBuYMCxidBTxXhoKhaM]
*: Whether we dwell in the '''thingness''' of fixity or the '''thingness''' of ''wujūd,'' we are “at” the ''wujūd'' of the Real.
* '''2002,''' Kai Hammermeister, ''The German Aesthetic Tradition'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&vid=ISBN0521785545&id=n4lGu9hu_ewC&pg=PA176&lpg=PA176&sig=QuC-Pn46rPB8OFi2S9KtvMmExh0]
*: The '''thingness''' of a thing precedes the conscious perception of its sensual properties.

